  "type": "mcq",
  "title": "Circular motion - to slow or not to slow",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two cars, Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, are going around the same horizontal curve. Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> maintains a constant speed throughout the turn, while Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> slows down at a constant rate. At the moment when both cars have the same speed, which car experiences a greater magnitude of acceleration and why?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. The acceleration of Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is zero because it moves with constant speed.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. The car’s acceleration is the vector sum of both tangential and centripetal accelerations.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. The centripetal acceleration of Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is less than that Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>’s because Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is slowing down.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. The centripetal acceleration of Car <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is partially canceled by its tangential deceleration.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
